49. Group Anagrams
Problem

Given an array of strings strs, group the anagrams together.

Two strings are anagrams if they contain the same characters with the same frequencies, only the order differs.

Return the groups in any order.

Example 1
Input: strs = ["eat","tea","tan","ate","nat","bat"]

Output:
[
  ["bat"],
  ["nat","tan"],
  ["ate","eat","tea"]
]
Example 2
Input: strs = [""]

Output:
[[""]]
Example 3
Input: strs = ["a"]

Output:
[["a"]]

Approach 1: Brute Force
Intuition

Compare every string with every other string.

Two strings are anagrams if their sorted forms are equal.

Use a visited array so each string is grouped only once.

Java
class Solution {
    public List<List<String>> groupAnagrams(String[] strs) {

        List<List<String>> ans = new ArrayList<>();
        boolean[] visited = new boolean[strs.length];

        for (int i = 0; i < strs.length; i++) {

            if (visited[i]) continue;

            List<String> group = new ArrayList<>();
            group.add(strs[i]);
            visited[i] = true;

            char[] ch1 = strs[i].toCharArray();
            Arrays.sort(ch1);

            for (int j = i + 1; j < strs.length; j++) {

                if (visited[j]) continue;

                char[] ch2 = strs[j].toCharArray();
                Arrays.sort(ch2);

                if (Arrays.equals(ch1, ch2)) {
                    group.add(strs[j]);
                    visited[j] = true;
                }
            }

            ans.add(group);
        }

        return ans;
    }
}
Complexity
Time: O(n² × k log k)
Space: O(n)

k = average string length

Approach 2: HashMap + Sorted String (Most Common)
Intuition

All anagrams become identical after sorting.

Example:

eat → aet
tea → aet
ate → aet

Use the sorted string as the key.

Store:

Sorted String → List of Original Strings

Java
class Solution {
    public List<List<String>> groupAnagrams(String[] strs) {

        HashMap<String, List<String>> map = new HashMap<>();

        for (String str : strs) {

            char[] ch = str.toCharArray();
            Arrays.sort(ch);

            String key = new String(ch);

            map.putIfAbsent(key, new ArrayList<>());
            map.get(key).add(str);
        }

        return new ArrayList<>(map.values());
    }
}
