Approach 3: HashMap + Character Frequency (Optimal)
Intuition

Instead of sorting each string, count the frequency of all 26 lowercase letters.

Example:

eat

a =1
e =1
t =1

Frequency array:

[1,0,0,0,1,0,0,...,1]

Convert this frequency array into a unique string key.

Anagrams will always generate the same key.

Java
class Solution {
    public List<List<String>> groupAnagrams(String[] strs) {

        HashMap<String, List<String>> map = new HashMap<>();

        for (String str : strs) {

            int[] freq = new int[26];

            for (char c : str.toCharArray()) {
                freq[c - 'a']++;
            }

            StringBuilder key = new StringBuilder();

            for (int count : freq) {
                key.append(count).append("#");
            }

            String k = key.toString();

            map.putIfAbsent(k, new ArrayList<>());
            map.get(k).add(str);
        }

        return new ArrayList<>(map.values());
    }
}
